  "education": {
    "market_education": {
      "summary_en": "U.S. equities advanced modestly on April 24, with the tech-heavy NASDAQ outperforming the broader S&P 500 as investors rotated back into growth and semiconductor names following a period of elevated volatility. A number of chip and AI-infrastructure stocks \u2014 including ARM, AMD, and NVDA \u2014 posted significant single-day gains, pushing RSI readings deep into overbought territory and signaling strong but potentially stretched momentum. The muted S&P 500 gain relative to NASDAQ suggests the rally remains concentrated in large-cap tech rather than broad market participation.",
